Here, then, is the fixed gulf. He said, “I am the resurrection.'' The Sadducees asked him, “In the resurrec— tion whose wife shall a woman be if the seven had her to wife? ''

Is it possible to conceive planes of thought further apart? We feel that the dog or horse which waits always on its master with loving eyes is nearer to the man's range of vision than were the Sadducees to Jesus.

They were not ignorant. The Jews were the one people on earth who gave laws to their conquerors, nay, to the world, and the Sadducees were the social and intellectual aristocracy of the Jews. They were responsible for the ship of state, and for the most part steered her wisely when they could control the fanaticism of Pharisee and zealot. They sprang from the heroes who had pur- chased freedom for a pure monotheism
